                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the American Red Cross</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence relative to
                    the present situation in Nicaragua, I beg to inform you that, the Department is
                    in receipt of a telegram from the American Minister at Managua, Nicaragua, dated
                    August 23rd in which he states [summary of telegram referred to].</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
